"""
Coding Agent -- JARVIS v0.5.1

Workflow:
  Phase 2 -- PLAN:
    Standard (complexity < 7):
      Layer 1: 4 AIs write independent plans (parallel)
      Layer 2: GLM-5 picks the best plan and improves it
    Deep (complexity >= 7 or !!deepcode):
      Layer 1: 4 AIs write independent plans (parallel)
      Layer 2: 4 AIs each pick the best plan, improve it (parallel)
      Layer 3: GLM-5 picks the best improved plan, improves it one final time
  Phase 3 -- IMPLEMENT: ONE GLM-5 coder, ONE call. The plan's steps become
               the AI's chain of thought — it works through step 1, writes
               edits, then step 2 using step 1's code, etc. All in one call.
  Phase 3.5 -- REVIEW: ONE GLM-5 reviewer sees ALL changed files together,
               verifies cross-file integration, uses [REFS:]/[LSP:] to check
               dependencies, fixes issues.
  Phase 4 -- TEST: optional (only if user asks)
  Phase 5 -- DELIVER: show diff, ask to apply

Research sharing: all tool lookups (REFS, LSP, SEARCH, CODE, etc.) are
cached in a shared research_cache dict. Results from planners are
pre-injected into coder/reviewer prompts so they don't re-search.
Parallel lookups are deduplicated with per-key asyncio locks.

Syntax checking: coder output is syntax-checked (Python compile, Node
--check, JSON parse, HTML tag balance, CSS brace balance). Errors are
fixed in-place by a focused SYNTAX_FIX_PROMPT — code is NOT rolled back.
Same syntax-fix loop applies to reviewer fixes.
"""

